column12: SITTING STANDING TRANSFER SYSTEM
column13: A system for moving an individual between different positions includes a frame (20) including a pivoted seat (40) for receiving and a drive system for at least partially supporting and moving an Individual between different positions. A control circuit (200) is coupled to the drive system and includes a processor programmed to control the drive system to selectively assist in moving an individual between different positions. The seat comprises a pair of seat sections (42, 44) and a pivot mount (60) to move the seat sections in a generally horizontal plane between a position immediately adjacent one another to a position spaced apart from each other to allow an individual to position her/himself between the seat sections and alternately shift her/his weight to allow an operator to position the seat sections under the individual.

column12: REAL TIME MANAGEMENT IN MANUFACTURING UNCONSOLIDATED COMPOSITE MATERIALS
column13: A system, apparatus, computer program product, and a method for manufacturing an unconsolidated composite material. Sensor data is received from a sensor system for a composite material manufacturing system. The sensor data is received during manufacturing an unconsolidated composite material by the composite material manufacturing system. A set of predicted properties is determined for a number of portions of the unconsolidated composite material using the sensor data. The set of predicted properties is for the number of portions of the unconsolidated composite material as a completed product. A corrective action is performed based on a quality level for the number of portions of the unconsolidated composite material.

column12: Apparatus and methods for ocular injection
column13: An apparatus includes a housing coupled to a medicament container, which is coupled to a needle. An injection assembly is disposed within the housing and includes an energy storage member and an actuation rod. A distal end portion of the actuation rod is disposed within the medicament container. The energy storage member can produce a force on a proximal end portion of the actuation rod sufficient to move the distal end portion of the actuation rod within the medicament container. This can convey at least a portion of a substance from the medicament container via the needle when a distal tip of the needle is disposed within a first region of a target location. The force is insufficient to move the distal end portion of the actuation rod within the medicament container when the distal tip of the needle is disposed within a second region of the target location.

column12: Property Prediction For Unconsolidated Composite Materials
column13: A method, apparatus, system, and computer program product for manufacturing an unconsolidated composite material. Sensor data is received from a sensor system for a composite material manufacturing system, wherein the sensor data is received during manufacturing of the unconsolidated composite material by the composite material manufacturing system. A set of predicted properties is determined for a number of portions of the unconsolidated composite material as completed from manufacturing by the composite material manufacturing system using the sensor data. A quality level for the number of portions of the unconsolidated composite material is identified based on the set of predicted properties for the number of portions of the unconsolidated composite material.

column12: Stabilized oral pharmaceutical composition
column13: An orally deliverable pharmaceutical composition comprising (a) a selective cyclooxygenase-2 inhibitory drug of formula (I), wherein R4 is hydrogen or a C1-4 alkyl or alkoxy group, X is N or CR5 where R5 is hydrogen or halogen, and Y and Z are independently carbon or nitrogen atoms defining adjacent atoms of a five- to six-membered ring that is unsubstituted or substituted at one or more positions with oxo, halo, methyl or halomethyl groups in a therapeutically and/or prophylactically effective amount and (b) a solvent liquid that comprises at least one pharmaceutically acceptable polyethylene glycol and at least one pharmaceutically acceptable free radical-scavenging antioxidant, wherein at least 15% by weight of the drug is in dissolved or solubilised form in the solvent liquid.

column12: COMPOSICION FARMACEUTICA ORAL ESTABILIZADA
column13: QUE COMPRENDE:a)UNA DROGA INHIBIDORA DE BAJA SOLUBILIDAD ACUOSA EN CANTIDAD PROFILACTICAMENTE EFECTIVA TAL COMO CYCLOOXYGENASA-2 SELECTIVA DE FORMULA (I), DONDE R4 ES H O UN GRUPO C1-4, ALQUILO, ALCOXI, X ES N O CR5, R5 ES H O HALOGENO, Y y Z SON CARBONOS INDEPENDIENTES O ATOMOS DE NITROGENO DEFINIENDO ATOMOS ADYACENTES DE UN ANILLO DE CINCO A SEIS MIEMBROS QUE NO ES SUSTITUIDO O SUSTITUIDO EN UNA O MAS POSICIONES CON GRUPOS OXO, HALO, METILO O HALOMETILO, CONSISTENTE DE ANILLOS DE CICLOPENTANONA, FURANONA, METILOPIRAZOLA ISOXAZOLA Y PIRIDINA, SELECCIONADA DICHA DROGA DE CELECOXIB, DERACOXIB, VALDECOXIB Y JTE-522; b)UN LIQUIDO SOLVENTE, QUE COMPRENDE: i)AL MENOS UN POLIETILENO GLICOL DE PESO MOLECULAR DE 100 A 10 000; ii)AL MENOS 0,01% A 5% DE UN RADICAL LIBRE DE BARRIDO ANTIOXIDANTE FARMACEUTICAMENTE ACEPTABLE SELECCIONADO DE VITAMINA E, ACIDO MALICO, SULFITO DE SODIO, PROPILO GALATO, ENTRE OTROS; iii)HIDROXIPROPILMETILCELULOSA COMO REDUCTOR DE TURBIDEZ, ACIDO OLEICO Y UN TERCIARIO AMINO COMO TRIETANOLAMINA Y DIMETILAMINOETANOL. DONDE, UNA PORCION SUSTANCIAL DE (a) ESTA EN FORMA DISUELTA O SOLUBILIZADA EN (b), COMPRENDIENDO (a) UN GRUPO FUNCIONAL AMINOSULFONILO, CAPAZ DE REACCIONAR CON UN POLIETILENO GLICOL PARA FORMAR UN COMPUESTO ADICIONAL

column12: Composição farmacêutica oral estabilizada
column13: "COMPOSIçãO FARMACêUTICA ORAL ESTABILIZADA". A invenção refere-se a uma composição farmacêutica oralmente distribuível proporcionada compreendendo uma droga compreendendo aminossulfonila, por exemplo, uma droga seletiva inibitória da ciclooxigenase-2 e um líquido solvente compreendendo um polietileno glicol e um ou mais antioxidantes para remoção de radical livre. Pelo menos uma parte substancial da droga está na forma dissolvida no líquido solvente. A composição tem propriedades de início rápido e é útil no tratamento de condições e distúrbios mediados pela ciclooxigenase-2.

column12: APPARATUS AND METHODS FOR OCULAR INJECTION
column13: An apparatus includes a housing coupled to a medicament container, which is coupled to a needle. An injection assembly is disposed within the housing and includes an energy storage member and an actuation rod. A distal end portion of the actuation rod is disposed within the medicament container. The energy storage member can produce a force on a proximal end portion of the actuation rod sufficient to move the distal end portion of the actuation rod within the medicament container. This can convey at least a portion of a substance from the medicament container via the needle when a distal tip of the needle is disposed within a first region of a target location. The force is insufficient to move the distal end portion of the actuation rod within the medicament container when the distal tip of the needle is disposed within a second region of the target location.

column12: APARELHO E MÉTODOS PARA INJEÇÃO OCULAR
column13: APARELHO E MÉTODOS PARA INJEÇÃO OCULAR. Trata-se de um aparelho que inclui um alojamento acoplado a um recipiente de medicamento que é acoplado a uma agulha. Uma montagem de injeção está disposta no interior do alojamento e inclui um membro de armazenamento de energia e uma haste de atuação. Uma porção de extremidade distal da haste de atuação está disposta no interior do recipiente de medicamento. O membro de armazenamento de energia pode produzir uma força sobre uma porção de extremidade proximal da haste de atuação suficiente para mover a porção de extremidade distal da haste de atuação no interior do recipiente de medicamento. Isso pode transportar pelo menos uma porção de uma substância a partir do recipiente de medicamento através da agulha quando uma ponta distal da agulha está disposta no interior de uma primeira região de uma localização-alvo. A força é insuficiente para mover a porção de extremidade distal da haste de atuação no interior do recipiente de medicamento quando a ponta distal da agulha está disposta no interior de uma segunda região da localização-alvo.

column12: APPARATUS AND METHODS FOR OCULAR INJECTION
column13: 장치는, 주사바늘에 커플링되는 약제 용기에 커플링된 하우징을 포함한다. 주사 조립체는 하우징 내에 배치되고, 에너지 저장 부재 및 작동 봉을 포함한다. 작동 봉의 원위 말단부는 약제 용기 내에 배치된다. 에너지 저장 부재는, 약제 용기 내에서 작동 봉의 원위 말단부를 이동시키기에 충분한 힘을 작동 봉의 근위 말단부에 생성할 수 있다. 이는 주사바늘의 원위 선단이 표적 위치의 제1 구역 내에 배치될 때 주사바늘을 통해 약제 용기로부터 물질의 적어도 일부를 운반할 수 있다. 상기 힘은, 주사바늘의 원위 선단이 표적 위치의 제2 구역 내에 배치될 때, 약제 용기 내에서 작동 봉의 원위 말단부를 이동시키기에는 불충분하다.

column12: APPARATUS FOR OCULAR INJECTION
column13: Устройство включает в себя корпус, соединенный с контейнером с лекарственным веществом, соединенным с иглой. Инъекционный узел расположен в корпусе и включает в себя энергонакопительный элемент и исполнительный стержень. Дистальный концевой участок исполнительного стержня расположен в контейнере с лекарственным веществом. Энергонакопительный элемент может создавать силу на проксимальном концевом участке исполнительного стержня, достаточную для перемещения дистального концевого участка исполнительного стержня в контейнере с лекарственным веществом. Это может обеспечить перенос по меньшей мере части вещества из контейнера с лекарственным веществом через иглу, когда дистальный кончик иглы расположен в первой области целевого места. Эта сила является недостаточной для перемещения дистального концевого участка исполнительного стержня в контейнере с лекарственным веществом, когда дистальный кончик иглы расположен во второй области целевого места.

column12: EYEBALL INJECTION DEVICE AND METHOD
column13: To provide an eyeball injection device and method.SOLUTION: A device of the present invention includes a housing connected to a medicine container, and the medicine container is connected to a needle. An injection assembly is disposed in the housing, and includes an energy storage member and an operation bar. A distal end part of the operation bar is disposed in the medicine container. The energy storage member can generate the force sufficient to move the distal end part of the operation bar in the medicine container, to a proximal end part of the operation bar. Thereby, when a distal tip of the needle is arranged in a first region at a target position, at least part of a material can be carried from the medicine container by the needle. When the distal tip of the needle is arranged in a second region at the target position, the force is insufficient to move the distal end part of the operation bar in the medicine container.SELECTED DRAWING: Figure 21

column12: APPARATUS AND METHODS FOR OCULAR INJECTION
column13: An apparatus includes a housing coupled to a medicament container, which is coupled to a needle. An injection assembly is disposed within the housing and includes an energy storage member and an actuation rod. A distal end portion of the actuation rod is disposed within the medicament container. The energy storage member can produce a force on a proximal end portion of the actuation rod sufficient to move the distal end portion of the actuation rod within the medicament container. This can convey at least a portion of a substance from the medicament container via the needle when a distal tip of the needle is disposed within a first region of a target location. The force is insufficient to move the distal end portion of the actuation rod within the medicament container when the distal tip of the needle is disposed within a second region of the target location.

column12: Apparatus and methods for ocular injection
column13: An apparatus includes a housing coupled to a medicament container, which is coupled to a needle. An injection assembly is disposed within the housing and includes an energy storage member and an actuation rod. A distal end portion of the actuation rod is disposed within the medicament container. The energy storage member can produce a force on a proximal end portion of the actuation rod sufficient to move the distal end portion of the actuation rod within the medicament container. This can convey at least a portion of a substance from the medicament container via the needle when a distal tip of the needle is disposed within a first region of a target location. The force is insufficient to move the distal end portion of the actuation rod within the medicament container when the distal tip of the needle is disposed within a second region of the target location.

column12: Apparatus and method for ocular injection
column13: An apparatus includes a housing coupled with a medicament container, the medicament container coupled with a needle. An injection assembly is disposed within the housing and includes an energy storage and an actuation lever. A distal end portion of the actuation lever is disposed within the medicament container. The energy store may generate a force on a proximal end portion of the actuation rod sufficient to move the distal end portion of the actuation rod within the medicament container. This may deliver at least a portion of a substance from the medicament container via the needle when the distal tip of the needle is disposed within a first region of a target location. When the distal tip of the needle is disposed within a second region of the target location, the force is insufficient to move the distal portion of the actuation rod within the medicament container.

column12: APPARATUS AND METHODS FOR OCULAR INJECTION
column13: 장치는, 주사바늘에 커플링되는 약제 용기에 커플링된 하우징을 포함한다. 주사 조립체는 하우징 내에 배치되고, 에너지 저장 부재 및 작동 봉을 포함한다. 작동 봉의 원위 말단부는 약제 용기 내에 배치된다. 에너지 저장 부재는, 약제 용기 내에서 작동 봉의 원위 말단부를 이동시키기에 충분한 힘을 작동 봉의 근위 말단부에 생성할 수 있다. 이는 주사바늘의 원위 선단이 표적 위치의 제1 구역 내에 배치될 때 주사바늘을 통해 약제 용기로부터 물질의 적어도 일부를 운반할 수 있다. 상기 힘은, 주사바늘의 원위 선단이 표적 위치의 제2 구역 내에 배치될 때, 약제 용기 내에서 작동 봉의 원위 말단부를 이동시키기에는 불충분하다.

column12: APPARATUS AND METHODS FOR OCULAR INJECTION
column13: Provided is an apparatus comprising: a housing configured to receive at least a portion of a medicament container, an adjustment member coupled to a puncture member, a hub defining a passageway configured to receive the puncture member, an actuation rod configured to move within the medicament container in response to a force on the actuation rod when the puncture member is disposed within a first region of the target tissue. The actuation rod is configured to have limited movement in response to the force when the puncture member is disposed within a second region of the target tissue, the force having a magnitude less than a threshold value.
column15: ANDINO RAFAEL VICTOR;;ZARNITSYN VLADIMIR;;BROOKS CHRISTOPHER JOHN;;YOO JESSE;;KAHUTE TRENT JOHN;;ARSENAULT JUSTIN WILLIAM;;TRETTIN DAVID JACKSON;;BAUER ANDREW KENT;;LEWIS STEPHANIE ELAINE

column12: Apparatus and methods for ocular injection
column13: An apparatus includes a housing coupled to a medicament container, which is coupled to a needle. An injection assembly is disposed within the housing and includes an energy storage member and an actuation rod. A distal end portion of the actuation rod is disposed within the medicament container. The energy storage member can produce a force on a proximal end portion of the actuation rod sufficient to move the distal end portion of the actuation rod within the medicament container. This can convey at least a portion of a substance from the medicament container via the needle when a distal tip of the needle is disposed within a first region of a target location. The force is insufficient to move the distal end portion of the actuation rod within the medicament container when the distal tip of the needle is disposed within a second region of the target location.

column12: EYEBALL INJECTION DEVICE AND METHOD
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide an eyeball injection device and method.SOLUTION: A device of the present invention includes a housing connected to a medicine container, and the medicine container is connected to a needle. An injection assembly is disposed in the housing, and includes an energy storage member and an operation bar. A distal end part of the operation bar is disposed in the medicine container. The energy storage member can generate the force sufficient to move the distal end part of the operation bar in the medicine container, to a proximal end part of the operation bar. Thereby, when a distal tip of the needle is arranged in a first region at a target position, at least part of a material can be carried from the medicine container by the needle. When the distal tip of the needle is arranged in a second region at the target position, the force is insufficient to move the distal end part of the operation bar in the medicine container.SELECTED DRAWING: Figure 21

column12: APPARATUS AND METHODS FOR OCULAR INJECTION
column13: Provided is an apparatus comprising: a housing configured to receive at least a portion of a medicament container, an adjustment member coupled to a puncture member, a hub defining a passageway configured to receive the puncture member, an actuation rod configured to move within the medicament container in response to a force on the actuation rod when the puncture member is disposed within a first region of the target tissue. The actuation rod is configured to have limited movement in response to the force when the puncture member is disposed within a second region of the target tissue, the force having a magnitude less than a threshold value.

column12: Apparatus and methods for ocular injection
column13: An apparatus includes a housing coupled to a medicament container, which is coupled to a needle. An injection assembly is disposed within the housing and includes an energy storage member and an actuation rod. A distal end portion of the actuation rod is disposed within the medicament container. The energy storage member can produce a force on a proximal end portion of the actuation rod sufficient to move the distal end portion of the actuation rod within the medicament container. This can convey at least a portion of a substance from the medicament container via the needle when a distal tip of the needle is disposed within a first region of a target location. The force is insufficient to move the distal end portion of the actuation rod within the medicament container when the distal tip of the needle is disposed within a second region of the target location.

column12: Carbamoyl compounds as DGAT1 inhibitors
column13: DGAT-1 inhibitor compounds of formula (I), pharmaceutically-acceptable salts and pro-drugs thereof are described, together with pharmaceutical compositions, processes for making them and their use in treating, for example, obesity wherein, for example, Ring A is optionally substituted 2, 6-pyrazindiyl; X is =O; Ring B is optionally substituted 1, 4-phenylene; Y1 is a direct bond or -O-; Y2 is -(CH2)r- wherein r is 2 or 3; n is 0 or n is 1 when Y1 is a direct bond between Ring B and Ring C and when Ring B is 1, 4-phenylene and Ring C is (4-6C)cycloalkane; Ring C is optionally substituted (4-6C)cycloalkane, (7-10C)bicycloalkane, (8-12C)tricycloalkane, phenylene or pryidindiyl; L is a direct bond or -O-; p is 0, 1 or 2 and when p is 1 RA1 and RA2 are each independently hydrogen or (1-4C)alkyl; Z is carboxy or a mimic or bioisostere thereof.

column12: Devices and Methods for Navigating Between User Interfaces
column13: An electronic device displays a plurality of user interface representations in a stack on a display. The device detects a first drag gesture by a first contact at a location on a touch-sensitive surface that corresponds to a location of a first user interface representation on the display. While the first contact is at a location on the touch-sensitive surface that corresponds to the location of the first user interface representation on the display and is moving across the touch-sensitive surface in a direction that corresponds to a first direction on the display, the device moves the first user interface representation in the first direction on the display at a first speed in accordance with a speed of the first contact on the touch-sensitive surface and moves a second user interface representation, disposed above the first user interface representation in the stack, in the first direction at a second speed greater than the first speed.

column12: Image alignment systems and methods
column13: Examples described herein include methods and systems for adjusting images which may be captured, for example, by a wearable camera. The wearable camera may be devoid of a viewfinder. Accordingly, it may be desirable to adjust images captured by the wearable camera prior to display to a user. Image adjustment techniques may employ physical wedges, calibration techniques, and/or machine learning techniques as described herein.

column12: Integrated work management engine for customer care in a communication system
column13: The present integrated work management engine for customer care orchestrates all forms of work relating to the servicing of customer requests across the entire business enterprise. This integrated work management engine brings together all types of disparate communication system components, applications and information storage systems so the business which provides the customer care via these systems can respond to their customer requests in a unified, efficient and effective manner. The integrated work management engine also integrates the real time operation of the front office customer communications and the batch data processing mode of the back office. The integrated work management engine accepts work through multiple access channels, where each work request is automatically mapped to a process flow that specifies the task associated with the handling of the particular work item. The integrated work management engine uses resource selection algorithms to select the customer agent who is best equipped to handle the next step of the work request where customer data is accessed, and customer case files are updated through the fulfillment process. The selected customer agent views the customer information, process information, forms, and performance statistics on their desktop terminal device through an API set that is tightly coupled to the integrated work management engine.

column12: Devices and methods for navigating between user interfaces
column13: An electronic device displays a plurality of user interface representations in a stack on a display. The device detects a first drag gesture by a first contact at a location on a touch-sensitive surface that corresponds to a location of a first user interface representation on the display. While the first contact is at a location on the touch-sensitive surface that corresponds to the location of the first user interface representation on the display and is moving across the touch-sensitive surface in a direction that corresponds to a first direction on the display, the device moves the first user interface representation in the first direction on the display at a first speed in accordance with a speed of the first contact on the touch-sensitive surface and moves a second user interface representation, disposed above the first user interface representation in the stack, in the first direction at a second speed greater than the first speed.

column12: Core structures for composite panels of an aircraft, composite panels and aircraft including the core structures, and methods of manufacturing the composite panels
column13: Core structures ( 120 ) for composite panels ( 75 ) of an aircraft ( 10 ), composite panels ( 75 ) and aircraft ( 10 ) including the core structures ( 120 ), and methods ( 200 ) of manufacturing the composite panels ( 75 ) are disclosed herein. The core structures ( 120 ) include a first side ( 140 ), a second side ( 150 ), and a connecting region ( 160 ) that interconnects an upper portion ( 142 ) of the first side ( 140 ) with an upper portion ( 152 ) of the second side ( 150 ). The first side ( 140 ), the second side ( 150 ), and the connecting region ( 160 ) at least partially define an antenna housing ( 62 ), which defines a housing volume ( 64 ) configured to contain an aircraft antenna ( 60 ) of the aircraft ( 10 ), and an electromagnetic wave transmission region ( 66 ) configured to permit electromagnetic waves to pass therethrough. The electromagnetic wave transmission region ( 66 ) defines a plurality of kite-shaped voids ( 130 ) arranged in a repeating pattern and bounded by a corresponding plurality of walls ( 170 ), at least 10% of which extends at least substantially perpendicular to a surface ( 122/124 ) that bounds the electromagnetic wave transmission region ( 66 ).

column12: INTEGRATED WORK MANAGEMENT ENGINE FOR CUSTOMER CARE IN A COMMUNICATION SYSTEM
column13: The present integrated work management engine orchestrates all forms of work relating to the servicing of customer requests across the entire business enterprise by integrating disparate communication system components, applications and information storage systems. The system also integrates the real time operation of the front office customer communications and the batch data processing mode of the back office. Work arrives on multiple access channels and is automatically mapped to a process flow that specifies the task and the customer agent who is best equipped to handle the work request.

column12: CORE STRUCTURES FOR COMPOSITE PANELS OF AN AIRCRAFT COMPOSITE PANELS AND AIRCRAFT INCLUDING THE CORE STRUCTURES AND METHODS OF MANUFACTURING THE COMPOSITE PANELS
column13: Disclosed are core structures (120) for complex panels (75) of an aircraft (10), an aircraft (10) including the core structures (120), and complex panels (75) and a method of manufacturing the complex panels (75). The core structures (120) include: a first lateral side (140); a second lateral side (150); and a connection area (160) connecting the upper part (152) of the second lateral side (150) and the upper part (142) of the first lateral side (140). The first lateral side (140), the second lateral side (150) and the connection area (160) define at least one part of an antenna housing (62) defining a housing volume (64) formed to include an aircraft antenna (60) of the aircraft (10), and define an electromagnetic wave delivery area (66) formed to let electromagnetic waves go therethrough. The electromagnetic wave delivery area (66) defines a plurality of edged openings arranged in repeated patterns, the edged openings (130) have a border with a plurality of corresponding walls (170), and at least 10 percent of the walls (170) extend substantially perpendicular from surfaces (122, 124) forming a border of the electromagnetic wave delivery area (66).

column12: DEVICES AND METHODS FOR NAVIGATING BETWEEN USER INTERFACES
column13: A method includes: displaying a first view of a first application; detecting a first portion of a first input; if the first portion of the first input meets application-switching criteria, concurrently displaying portions of the first application view and a second application view; while concurrently displaying the portions of the application views, detecting a second portion of the first input; if the second portion of the first input meets first-view display criteria (liftoff of contact detected in a first region), ceasing to display the portion of the second application view and displaying the first application view; and if the second portion of the first input meets multi-view display criteria (liftoff of contact detected in a second region), maintaining concurrent display of a portion of the first application view and a portion of the second application view on the display after detecting the liftoff of the contact.

column12: Devices and Methods for Navigating Between User Interfaces
column13: An electronic device displays a plurality of user interface representations in a stack on a display. The device detects a first drag gesture by a first contact at a location on a touch-sensitive surface that corresponds to a location of a first user interface representation on the display. While the first contact is at a location on the touch-sensitive surface that corresponds to the location of the first user interface representation on the display and is moving across the touch-sensitive surface in a direction that corresponds to a first direction on the display, the device moves the first user interface representation in the first direction on the display at a first speed in accordance with a speed of the first contact on the touch-sensitive surface and moves a second user interface representation, disposed above the first user interface representation in the stack, in the first direction at a second speed greater than the first speed.

column12: IMAGE ALIGNMENT SYSTEMS AND METHODS
column13: Examples described herein include methods and systems for adjusting images which may be captured, for example, by a wearable camera. The wearable camera may be devoid of a viewfinder. Accordingly, it may be desirable to adjust images captured by the wearable camera prior to display to a user. Image adjustment techniques may employ physical wedges, calibration techniques, and/or machine learning techniques as described herein.

column13: estruturas de núcleo (120) para painéis compósitos (75) de uma aeronave (10), painéis compósitos (75) e aeronave (10) incluindo as estruturas de núcleo (120), e métodos (200) para fabricar os painéis compósitos (75) são descritos aqui. as estruturas de núcleo (120) incluem um primeiro lado (140), um segundo lado (150) e uma região de conexão (160) que interconecta uma porção superior (142) do primeiro lado (140) com uma porção superior (152) do segundo lado (150). o primeiro lado (140), o segundo lado (150) e a região de conexão (160) definem pelo menos parcialmente um alojamento de antena (62), que define um volume do alojamento (64) configurado para conter uma antena de aeronave (60) da aeronave (10), e uma região de transmissão de ondas eletromagnéticas (66) configurada para permitir que ondas eletromagnéticas passe através da mesma. a região de transmissão de ondas eletromagnéticas (66) define uma pluralidade de vazios em formato de pipa (130) arranjados em um padrão repetitivo e delimitados por uma pluralidade correspondente de paredes (170), pelo menos 10% das quais se estende pelo menos substancialmente perpendicular a uma superfície (122/124) que delimita a região de transmissão de ondas eletromagnéticas (66).

column12: CALL CENTER WITH INTEGRATED WORK MANAGEMENT
column13: The present integrated work management engine orchestrates all forms of work relating to the servicing of customer requests across the entire business enterprise by integrating disparate communication system components, applications and information storage systems. The system also integrates the real time operation of the front office customer communications and the batch data processing mode of the back office. Work arrives on multiple access channels and is automatically mapped to a process flow that specifies the task and the customer agent who is best equipped to handle the work request.

column12: Medical environment event parsing system
column13: A system and a method are described for identifying (e.g., parsing images) images pertaining to an event. The method also includes identifying a first subset of pixels from the plurality of potential locations as representing a bed and/or a seating platform. The method also includes identifying a second subset of pixels within the field of view of the camera as representing an object proximal to the bed and/or seating platform. The method also includes determining an orientation of the object with respect to the bed and/or seating platform, and determining changes in the orientation and/or position of the object over a period of time. In implementations, the method further includes generating state data pertaining to an event and associating the state data with corresponding image frame data.

column12: Medical environment monitoring system
column13: A system and a method are described for monitoring a medical care environment. In one or more implementations, a method includes identifying a first subset of pixels within a field of view of a camera as representing a bed. The method also includes identifying a second subset of pixels within the field of view of the camera as representing an object (e.g., a subject, such as a patient, medical personnel; bed; chair; patient tray; medical equipment; etc.) proximal to the bed. The method also includes determining an orientation of the object within the bed. In implementations, the method further includes issuing an electronic communication alert based upon the orientation of the object, and determining whether to issue future alerts based upon feedback to the alert.

column12: Medical environment monitoring system
column13: A system and a method are described for monitoring a medical care environment. In one or more implementations, a method includes identifying a first subset of pixels within a field of view of a camera as representing a bed. The method also includes identifying a second subset of pixels within the field of view of the camera as representing an object (e.g., a patient) proximal to the bed. The method also includes determining an orientation of the object within the bed. In implementations, the method further includes issuing an electronic communication notification directing a user to view a display monitor associated with the object based upon the orientation of the object. In some implementations, the method further includes breaking out a particular portion of the display associated with the object. In some implementations, the method also includes determining whether to issue future notifications based upon feedback to the notification.

column12: Apparatus and methods for ocular injection
column13: An apparatus includes a housing coupled to a medicament container, which is coupled to a needle. An injection assembly is disposed within the housing and includes an energy storage member and an actuation rod. A distal end portion of the actuation rod is disposed within the medicament container. The energy storage member can produce a force on a proximal end portion of the actuation rod sufficient to move the distal end portion of the actuation rod within the medicament container. This can convey at least a portion of a substance from the medicament container via the needle when a distal tip of the needle is disposed within a first region of a target location. The force is insufficient to move the distal end portion of the actuation rod within the medicament container when the distal tip of the needle is disposed within a second region of the target location.

column12: Medical environment bedsore detection and prevention system

The method also includes identifying a first subset of pixels from the plurality of potential locations as representing a bed and/or a seating platform. The method also includes identifying a second subset of pixels within the field of view of the camera as representing an object (e.g., a subject, such as a patient, medical personnel; bed; chair; patient tray; medical equipment; etc.) proximal to the bed and/or seating platform. The method also includes determining an orientation of the object with respect to the bed and/or seating platform, and determining changes in the orientation and/or position of the object over a period of time. In implementations, the method further includes issuing an electronic communication alert based upon the determined orientation and/or position of the object over the period of time.

column13: Un compuesto de la fórmula (I), o una sal farmacéuticamente aceptable, o un profármaco del mismo,**Fórmula** en donde el Anillo A es 2,6-pirazindiilo sustituido opcionalmente sobre un átomo de carbono disponible por uno o dos sustituyentes seleccionados independientemente de (1-3C)alquilo, (2-3C)alquenilo, (2-3C)alquinilo, (1-2C)alcoxi, metoximetilo, amino y ciano lineales; X es >=O o >=S; el Anillo B es 1,4-fenileno sustituido opcionalmente sobre un átomo de carbono disponible por uno o dos sustituyentes seleccionados independientemente de halo, amino, ciano, (1-4C)alquilo, (2-3C)alquenilo, (2- 3C)alquinilo, (1-4C)alcoxi y (1-4C)alcoxi-(1-4C)alquilo; Y1 es un enlace directo entre el Anillo B y el Anillo C o Y1 es -O-, -S- o -NRa- en donde Ra es hidrógeno o (1- 4C)alquilo; Y2 es -(CH2)r- en donde r es 2 o 3, e Y2 está enlazado al mismo átomo de carbono que Y1 en el Anillo C e Y2 está enlazado a un átomo de carbono adyacente a Y1 en el Anillo B; n es 0 o n es 1 cuando Y1 es un enlace directo entre el Anillo B y el Anillo C y cuando el Anillo B es 1,4-fenileno y el Anillo C es (4-6C)cicloalcano, de manera que se forma un sistema de anillo espiro de 5 o 6 miembros y el Anillo C es trienlazado; El Anillo C es un anillo o sistema de anillo dienlazado (excluyendo enlaces a través de los mismos átomos o adyacentes) escogido de entre (4-6C)cicloalcano, (7-10C)bicicloalcano y (8-12C)tricicloalcano cada uno sustituido opcionalmente sobre un átomo de carbono disponible, incluyendo el átomo de carbono de anillo que porta el grupo que contiene Z, por un sustituyente seleccionado de entre hidroxi, (1-4C)alquilo, (1-4C)alcoxi y (1-4C)alcoxi(1- 4C)alquilo; o el Anillo C es un anillo o sistema de anillo dienlazado (excluyendo enlaces a través de los mismos enlaces o adyacentes) seleccionado de entre fenileno, piridindiilo, piperidinadiilo Enlazado en N a Y1, piperazinediilo, furandiilo, tiofendiilo, pirroldiilo, oxazoldiilo, tiazoldiilo, imidazoldiilo, isoxazoldiilo, isotiazoldiilo, pirazoldiilo y azabiciclo[3.1.0]hexanodiilo; cada uno sustituido opcionalmente sobre un átomo de carbono disponible por hasta cuatro sustituyentes seleccionados independientemente de entre fluoro, cloro, bromo, ciano, (1-4C)alquilo, (1-4C)alcoxi y (1-4C)alcoxi(1- 4C)alquilo; L es un enlace directo al Anillo C, -O-, -S- o -NH-; p es 0 (cuando L es un enlace directo), 1 o 2 y cuando p es 1 o 2 RA1 y RA2 son cada uno independientemente hidrógeno o (1-4C)alquil o RA1 y RA2 están enlazados entre sí para formar un anillo (3-6C)espiroalquilo; Z es carboxi o un imitador o bioisóstero del mismo, hidroxi o -CONRbRc en donde Rb y Rc son seleccionados independientemente de entre hidrógeno y (1-4C)alquilo, grupo alquilo (1-4C) que puede ser sustituido opcionalmente por carboxi o un imitador o bioisóstero del mismo; y en donde cualquier átomo de carbono en un grupo que contiene(1-3C)alquilo, (1-2C)alcoxi, (1-4C)alquil o (1- 4C)alcoxi lineales definidos más arriba puede ser sustituido opcionalmente por hasta 3 átomos de flúor; en donde un imitador o un bioisóstero de un grupo carboxi es seleccionado de entre -SO3H, -S(O)2NHR13, S(O)2NHC(O)R13, -CH2S(O)2R13, -C(O)NHS(O)2R1340 , -C(O)NHOH, -C(O)NHCN, -CH(CF3)OH, C(CF3)2OH, -P(O)(OH)2 y grupos de la subfórmula (a)-(i') más abajo**Fórmula** en donde cuando p en la subfórmula (k) es 1 o 2, R27 y R28 son seleccionados independientemente de entre hidrógeno, hidroxi, (1-6C)alcoxi, tiol, (1-6C)alquiltio, -C(O)R29, -S(O)R30, -SO2R31, -NR32R33, -NHCN, halógeno y trihalometilo, donde R29, R30 y R31 son -OR34, (1-6C)alquilo, -NR32R33 o trihalometilo, R32 y R33 son seleccionados independientemente de entre hidrógeno, (1-6C)alquilo, -SO2R34 y - COR35, donde R35 es (1-6C)alquil o trihalometilo, y R34 es hidrógeno, (1-6C)alquil o trihalometil y R13 es seleccionado de entre hidrógeno, (1-6C)alquilo, hidroxi, halo, amino, ciano, ((1-3C)alquil)CONH-, carboxi, (1-6C)alcoxi, (1-6C)alcoxicarbonilo, carbamoilo, N- ((1- 6C)alquil)carbamoilo, halo((1-6C)alquil) (tal como trifluorometilo), (1-6C)alquilsulfonil o (1-6C)alquilsulfinilo; y en donde un profármaco del mismo es un éster de un grupo carboxi seleccionado de entre un (1-6C)alquiléster, un (1-6C)alcoximetiléster, un (1-6C)alcanoiloximetiléster, un ftalidiléster, un (3-8C)cicloalcoxicarboniloxi(1- 6C)alquiléster, un 1,3-dioxolan-2-ilmetiléster, un (1-6C)alcoxicarboniloxietiléster, un aminocarbonilmetiléster y una versión mono- o di-N-((1-6C)alquil) de un aminocarbonilmetil éster.

column12: Modular fuel cell system architecture and control system to distribute power to modules
column13: The invention relates to a modular fuel cell system architecture and a control system to distribute power to modules. Systems and methods for modularizing a system are provided. Parallel power systems with electrically isolated high voltage systems facilitate modularization. A control system is provided that optimizes the distribution of power demand and/or torque requests in order to maintain the efficiency, durability, drivability and/or safety of the system within optimal ranges. In some cases, the distribution of power is non-uniform in order to extend battery life, while in other cases, the power draw across the battery system remains equal and constant in order to appropriately manage the state of charge of the parallel power system. In other cases, the selected power distribution maintains the power demand and/or torque request between minimum and maximum levels/capacities, and the power distribution avoids on/off of a single power system.

column12: COMPOSITE CLEANING PRODUCTS HAVING SHAPE RESILIENT LAYER
column13: The present invention discloses a disposable cleaning product for use in household cleaning or personal care applications. The cleaning product (10) of the invention is a multi-layer laminate product and may include at least two distinct layers, an abrasive layer (12) and an absorbent layer (16). The absorbent layer contains a sponge-like member (20) optionally in combination with a plurality of cellulosic fibrous webs (18). The sponge-like member can be made from various materials. For example, in one embodiment, the sponge-like member comprises one or more layers of a spunbond web containing crimped, bicomponent filaments.

column12: produtos de limpeza de compósito tendo camada resiliente moldada
column13: PRODUTOS DE LIMPEZA DE COMPóSITO TENDO CAMADA RESILIENTE MOLDADA. A presente invenção descreve um produto de limpeza disponível para uso em limpeza de casa ou aplicações de cuidado pessoais. O produto de limpeza (10) da invenção é um produto laminado multicamada é pode incluir pelo menos duas camadas distintas, uma camada abrasiva (12) e uma camada absorvente (16) . A camada absorvente contém um membro tipo esponja (20) opcionalmente em combinação com uma pluralidade de telas fibrosas celulósicas (18) . O membro do tipo esponja pode ser feito de vários materiais. Por exemplo, em uma modalidade, o membro tipo esponja compreende um ou mais camadas de uma tela não tecida contendo enrugados, filamentos de bicomponente.

column13: A mobile phone may include a housing, a battery at least partially within the housing, and a circuit board assembly at least partially within the housing and positioned along a side of the battery. The circuit board assembly may include a first circuit board defining a first hole, a second circuit board defining a second hole, a wall structure between the first circuit board and the second circuit board and attached to an inner surface of the first circuit board and an inner surface of the second circuit board, and a fastener assembly configured to retain the first circuit board to the second circuit board.

column12: DEVICES AND METHODS FOR NAVIGATING BETWEEN USER INTERFACES
column13: A method includes: displaying a first view of a first application; detecting a first portion of a first input; if the first portion of the first input meets application-switching criteria, concurrently displaying portions of the first application view and a second application view; while concurrently displaying the portions of the application views, detecting a second portion of the first input; if the second portion of the first input meets first-view display criteria (liftoff of contact detected in a first region), ceasing to display the portion of the second application view and displaying the first application view; and if the second portion of the first input meets multi-view display criteria (liftoff of contact detected in a second region), maintaining concurrent display of a portion of the first application view and a portion of the second application view on the display after detecting the liftoff of the contact.

column12: Devices and methods for navigating between user interfaces
column13: The present disclosure provides devices and methods for navigating between user interfaces. An electronic device includes a display unit, a touch-sensitive surface unit, and a processing unit. The processing unit enables displaying a plurality of user interface representations in a heap on a display unit. A second user interface representation is offset from the first user interface representation in the first direction to partially expose the first user interface representation. The processing unit is configured to detect a first drag gesture through the first contact. The processing unit is further configured to: when the first contact moves across the touch-sensitive surface unit at a position on the touch-sensitive surface unit corresponding to a position of the first user interface representation on the display unit and in a direction corresponding to a first direction on the display unit, move the first user interface representation in a first direction at a first speed according to the speed of the first contact; and move the second user interface representation disposed above the first user interface representation in the first direction at a second speed greater than the first speed.

column13: 방법은, 제1 애플리케이션의 제1 뷰를 표시하는 것; 제1 입력의 제1 부분을 검출하는 것; 제1 입력의 제1 부분이 애플리케이션-스위칭 기준을 충족시키는 경우, 제1 애플리케이션 뷰 및 제2 애플리케이션 뷰의 부분들을 동시에 표시하는 것; 애플리케이션 뷰들의 부분들을 동시에 표시하는 동안, 제1 입력의 제2 부분을 검출하는 것; 상기 제1 입력의 제2 부분이 제1-뷰 표시 기준(제1 영역에서 검출된 접촉의 리프트오프)을 충족시키는 경우, 제2 애플리케이션 뷰의 부분을 표시하는 것을 중지하고 제1 애플리케이션 뷰를 표시하는 것; 및 제1 입력의 제2 부분이 멀티-뷰 표시 기준(제2 영역에서 검출된 접촉의 리프트오프)을 충족시키는 경우, 접촉의 리프트오프를 검출한 후에 디스플레이 상에 제1 애플리케이션 뷰의 일부분 및 제2 애플리케이션 뷰의 일부분의 동시 표시를 유지하는 것을 포함한다.

column12: Devices and methods for navigating between user interfaces
column13: The disclosure provides devices and methods for navigating between user interfaces. An electronic device comprises a display, a touch-sensitive surface, and one or more sensors to detect intensity of contacts. The processing unit is configured as displaying, on the display, a user interface for an application; detecting an edge input that includes detecting a change in a characteristic intensity of a contact proximate to an edge of the touch-sensitive surface; and, in response to detecting the edge input: in accordance with a determination that the edge input meets system-gesture criteria, performing an operation that is independent of the application, wherein: the system-gesture criteria include intensity criteria; the system-gesture criteria include a location criterion that is met when the intensity criteria for the contact are met while the contact is within a first region relative to the touch-sensitive surface; and the first region relative to the touch-sensitive surface is determined based on one or more characteristics of the contact.

column12: DEVICE AND METHOD FOR NAVIGATING BETWEEN INTERFACES
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a more quick, more efficient method for navigating between interfaces.SOLUTION: A method includes: displaying a first view of a first application; detecting a first portion of a first input; when the first portion of the first input satisfies an application changing standard, simultaneously displaying portions of a first application view and a second application view; detecting a second portion of the first input while simultaneously displaying the portions of the application views; when the second portion of the first input satisfies a first view display standard, stopping display of a portion of the second application view and displaying the first application view; and when the second portion of the first input satisfies a multi-view display standard, detecting lift-off of contact before maintaining simultaneous display of a portion of the first application view and a portion of the second application view on a display.SELECTED DRAWING: Figure 25A

column12: Device and method for navigating between user interfaces
column13: The invention provides a device and method for navigating between user interfaces. An electronic device comprises a display unit, a touch-sensitive surface unit and a processing unit. The processing unit achieves representation of multiple user interfaces in a stack in the display unit. A second user interface represents deviation from a first user interface in a first direction and partially exposes representation of the first user interface. The processing unit is configured to detect a first dragging gesture passing first touch. The processing unit is also configured to represent movement of the first user interface according to speed of first touch at first speed in a first direction and represent the second user interface movably arranged above the first user interface in the first direction at second speed being greater than the first speed at the position corresponding to the position representing the first user interface of the display unit of the touch-sensitive unit of the first touch and when the touch-sensitive surface unit moves in a direction corresponding to the first direction on the display unit.

column12: DEVICE AND METHOD FOR NAVIGATING BETWEEN USER INTERFACES
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide an efficient user interface transition method.SOLUTION: A processing unit validates display of a first view of a first application on a display unit, performs detection of a first part of a first input containing detection of a first contact on a touch sensing surface unit in a period in which display of the first view is effective, and validates simultaneous display of parts of plural application views containing a first application view and second application view on the display unit according to determination that the first part of the first input satisfies an application changeover reference according to detection of the first part of the first input. In the period in which the simultaneous display of the parts of the plural application views is effective, a second part of the first input containing lift-off of the first contact is detected.SELECTED DRAWING: Figure 27

column12: Devices and methods for navigating between user interfaces

column12: DEVICES AND METHODS FOR NAVIGATING BETWEEN USER INTERFACES
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide an electronic device that allows for navigating between user interfaces.SOLUTION: A method includes: displaying a first application view 508; detecting a first portion of a first input; concurrently displaying portions of the first application view and a second application view 510 if the first portion of the first input meets application-switching criteria; detecting a second portion of the first input while concurrently displaying the portions of the application views; if the second portion of the first input meets first-view display criteria, ceasing to display the portion of the second application view and displaying the first application view; and, if the second portion of the first input meets multi-view display criteria, maintaining concurrent display of the portion of the first application view and the portion of the second application view on the display after detecting the liftoff of the contact.SELECTED DRAWING: Figure 22C

column12: Apparatus and method for navigating between user interfaces
column13: The present disclosure provides an apparatus and method for navigating between user interfaces. An electronic device includes a display unit, a touch-sensitive surface unit, and a processing unit. The processing unit enables displaying a plurality of user interface representations in a heap on a display unit. The second user interface representation is offset from the first user interface representation in the first direction, thereby partially exposing the first user interface representation. The processing unit is configured to detect a first drag gesture through the first contact. The processing unit is further configured to when the first contact moves across the touch-sensitive surface unit at a position on the touch-sensitive surface unit corresponding to a position represented by a first user interface on the display unit and in a direction corresponding to a first direction on the display unit, move the first user interface representation in a first direction at a first speed according to the speed of the first contact; and move the second user interface representation disposed above the first user interface representation in the first direction at a second speed greater than the first speed.

column12: device and a method of navigation between user interfaces
column13: The invention provides a device and a method of navigation between user interfaces. An electronic device includes: a display unit, a touch sense surface unit, and a processing unit. The processing unit displays a plurality of user interface display on a stack in the display unit. The second user interface expression is deflected from the first user interface expression in the first direction, and partially exposes the first user interface expression. The processing unit detects a first drag gesture that passes through the first touch and also moves the first user interface expression at a first speed in the first direction according to the first touch speed when the first touch is moved at the position that is corresponding to the position of the first user interface expression of the first touch on the touch-sense surface unit and the display unit and to across the touch sense surface unit in accordance with a first direction on the display unit, and moves the second user interface expression that is above the first user interface expression at the second speed that is higher than the first speed in the first direction.

column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide electronic devices based on faster and more efficient methods and interfaces for navigating between user interfaces.SOLUTION: Portions of a first application view 508 and a second application view 510 are concurrently displayed and, if an input meets first-view display criteria (liftoff of contact detected in a first region), the portion of the second application view ceases to be displayed and the first application view continues to be displayed, whereas if the input meets multi-view display criteria (liftoff of contact detected in a second region), concurrent display of the portion of the first application view and the portion of the second application view is maintained on the display after detecting the liftoff of the contact.SELECTED DRAWING: Figure 22C

column12: DEVICE AND METHOD FOR NAVIGATING BETWEEN USER INTERFACES
column13: To provide a quick and efficient method for navigating between user interfaces.SOLUTION: The method comprises: while displaying a first user interface on a display, detecting an edge input including motion of a first contact traversing a touch sensing surface, the edge input being an input by the first contact to the touch sensing surface; displaying at least one of second user interface expression and a first user interface expression on the display while detecting the edge input by the first contact; and according to detecting finish of the input by the first contact, if the first contact moves by an amount larger than a first threshold amount in an orientation corresponding to a prescribed first orientation on the display, displaying a second user interface, and if the first contact does not move by the amount larger than the first threshold amount, displaying the first user interface again.SELECTED DRAWING: Figure 11A

column12: Devices and methods for navigating between user interfaces
column13: A method is performed at an electronic device with a display, a touch-sensitive surface, and one or more sensors to detect intensity of contacts. The method includes displaying, on the display, a user interface for an application; detecting an edge input that includes detecting a change in a characteristic intensity of a contact proximate to an edge of the touch-sensitive surface; and, in response to detecting the edge input: in accordance with a determination that the edge input meets system-gesture criteria, performing an operation that is independent of the application, wherein: the system-gesture criteria include intensity criteria; the system gesture criteria include a location criterion that is met when the intensity criteria for the contact are met while the contact is within a first region relative to the touch-sensitive surface; and the first region relative to the touch-sensitive surface is determined based on one or more characteristics of the contact.

column12: Portable electronic device and mobile phone
column13: The invention relates to a portable electronic device and a mobile phone. A portable electronic device may include a housing having walls, the housing defining an opening in the housing and at least a portion of four side surfaces of the portable electronic device. The portable electronic device may also include a display at least partially located within the housing; a front cover positioned in an opening in the housing and positioned over the display, the front cover defining a front surface, a peripheral side surface extending from the front surface and at least partially surrounded by a wall of the housing, and a recess, the recess, together with a portion of the wall of the housing, defines an acoustic port of the portable electronic device. The electronic device may also include an acoustic port cover positioned at least partially in the acoustic port, and a speaker positioned at least partially within the housing and configured to direct sound through the acoustic port cover.
